channel.title: Pictures from our trip to Alaska, the southwest, and back
channel.description: Most of the pages you are about to see depict landscapes, glorious unspoilt vistas stretching into the horizon at national parks and other lovely places. Most of the time, however, we were trapped inside a cramped climate-changing vehicle. Passenger trains were not really an option: service was infrequent and prices prohibitive. We decided to document some of the realities of the road here, thus putting the other pages in perspective. Much of what is beautiful and worthwhile is so because it is void of the banality and obscenity of highways, parking lots, malls, and suburban development. Think about it.
